Enzyme-ka loo yaqaan 'angiotensin-converting enzyme 2' (ACE2) waa enzyme ku xidhan dusha sare ee unugyada (xidhmooyinka unugyada) ee sanbabada, wadnaha, kelyaha iyo mindhicirka.
ACE2 waxay ka hortagtaa waxqabadka enzyme-ka angiotensin-converting enzyme (ACE) oo la xiriira yareynta tirada angiotensin-II iyo kordhinta Ang ((1-7) taas oo ka dhigaysa daawo la filayo in lagu beegsado daaweynta cudurada wadnaha.
Nooca aadanaha ee enzyme-ka waxaa badanaa loo yaqaan hACE2.
Angiotensin converting enzyme 2 waa zinc-ka ku jira metaloenzyme-ka ku yaal dusha sare ee unugyada iyo unugyada kale.
Badeecada ACE2 waxay ka kooban tahay N-terminal M2 peptidase domain iyo C-terminal renal amino acid transporter domain ee colectin.
ACE2 waa borotiinka xarkaha ee nooca 1 ee wadada kaliya, oo leh domain enzymatic ah oo si firfircoon ugu muuqda unugyada sanbabada iyo unugyada kale.
Xuduudda ka baxsan unugyada ACE2 waxaa ku dhegan xuduudda transmembrane ee enzymes kale oo loo yaqaan sheddase, waxaana protein-ka la kala bixiyay loo sii daayaa dhiigga ugu dambeynna waxaa loo sii daayaa kaadida.
ACE2 waxay ku jirtaa xubnaha badankood: ACE2 waxay ku xidhan tahay unugyada unugyada ee unugyada ugu badan ee nooca II ee sanbabada, unugyada xiidmaha yaryar ee unugyada, unugyada wadnaha iyo unugyada xajmiga iyo unugyada muruqyada jilicsan ee wadnaha ee unugyada badankood.
Muuqaalka mRNA ee ACE2 waxaa sidoo kale laga helaa qalfoofka maskaxda, striatum, hypothalamus iyo jirka.
Waxqabadka ugu weyn ee ACE2 waa in ay u dhaqmaan sidii dheelitirayaal ACE.
ACE waxay ku dhejisaa hormoonka angiotensin I ee ku jira angio-taangiotensin II.
ACE2 waxay ku xirantahay phenylalanine amino acid-ka karboksil-terminal ee angiotensin II (Asp-Arg-Val-Tyr-Ile-His-Pro-Phe) waxayna ku dhejisaa hydrolysis-ka angiotensin vasodilator (1-7), (H-Asp-Arg-Val-Tyr-Ile-His-Pro-OH).
ACE2 waxay sidoo kale ku dhejin kartaa tiro kale oo peptide ah oo ay ku jiraan [des-Arg9]- bradikinin, apelin, neurotensin, dinorphine A iyo ghrelin.
ACE2 waxay sidoo kale xakameysaa qaybinta xuubka ee SLC6A19 oo ah amino acid neutral oo loo yaqaan 'neutral amino acid transporter' waxaana lagu muujiyaa cudurka Hartnup.
Sida borotiinka transmembrane, ACE2 wuxuu u shaqeeyaa sida xarunta ugu weyn ee gelitaanka unugyada qaar ka mid ah cudurrada loo yaqaan 'coronavirus' oo ay ku jiraan HCoV-NL63; SARS-CoV (virus-ka sababa SARS); iyo SARS-CoV-2 (virus-ka sababa COVID-19).
Gaar ahaan, isku xirnaanta borotiinka S1 ee SARS-CoV iyo SARS-CoV2 ee domain-ka enzymatic ee ACE2 ee dusha sare ee unugyada waxay keentaa endocytosis iyo wareejinta fayraska iyo enzymes-ka ee ku yaal gudaha unugyada.
Nidaamka gelitaanka wuxuu sidoo kale u baahan yahay in borotiinka S uu ku soo kordho TMPRSS2 serine prosthesis, oo ah xakameynayaashu ay hadda ku jiraan daraasad caafimaad oo suurtagal ah.
Si kastaba ha ahaatee, ururada xirfadeed iyo hay'adaha sharciyeynta ayaa ku talinaya in la sii wado daaweynta ACE ee caadiga ah iyo daaweynta ARB.
Dib u eegis nidaamsan iyo falanqayn meta oo la daabacay July 11, 2012 ayaa lagu ogaaday in "isticmaalka ACE inhibitor ay la xiriiraan hoos u dhac weyn oo ah 34% khatarta sambabada marka loo eego kontaroolada".
Intaa waxaa dheer, "halista cudurka sambabada ayaa sidoo kale hoos u dhacday bukaannada la daaweeyay ACE inhibitors kuwaas oo halis sare u leh cudurka sambabada, gaar ahaan kuwa qaba cudurka istaroogga iyo wadnaha oo fashilmay.
Isticmaalka ACE inhibitors ayaa sidoo kale la xiriira hoos u dhac ku yimid dhimashada cudurka sambabada, inkastoo go'aanku uu ka liita guud ahaan halista sambabada".
